WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:03.070
Good morning family, how are y'all doing

00:00:03.080 --> 00:00:05.990
today? Well, praise the Lord, I have Diana

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.430
with me again and we are just excited to

00:00:09.440 --> 00:00:11.470
be here. You know, we're just seeking the

00:00:11.480 --> 00:00:13.589
Lord together and we've been reading

00:00:13.599 --> 00:00:17.790
this book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near'. Yeah,

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:20.830
it's amazing and it is

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:23.269
phenomenal. We were just

00:00:23.279 --> 00:00:26.150
like scavengers, folks; we will

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:28.870
look through wherever we can to find a

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:31.589
good meal with the Lord. You know, if

00:00:31.599 --> 00:00:32.950
you don't feel like you're getting

00:00:32.960 --> 00:00:35.030
spiritually fed all the time in certain

00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:37.709
areas, you've got to find what it

00:00:37.709 --> 00:00:37.719
is.

00:00:37.719 --> 00:00:40.270
You can't just be lazy; you can't

00:00:40.280 --> 00:00:43.069
just depend on your pastor to feed you

00:00:43.079 --> 00:00:45.430
all the time. You've got to be bold

00:00:45.440 --> 00:00:47.310
enough and strong enough to go out there and

00:00:47.320 --> 00:00:48.830
say, 'Listen, I'm going to find me

00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:50.590
something today, whatever I need in my

00:00:50.590 --> 00:00:50.600
life.'Does

00:00:50.600 --> 00:00:51.910
that make sense? Yeah, not just

00:00:51.920 --> 00:00:53.990
on Wednesdays and

00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:54.000
Sundays—every

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.430
day. Find something. You

00:00:56.440 --> 00:00:58.029
get your food on Sunday, you get your

00:00:58.039 --> 00:00:59.549
food on Wednesday, and if that's all you

00:00:59.559 --> 00:01:01.990
feed your spirit, your flesh eats every

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:04.590
day, three times a day. If you feed your

00:01:04.600 --> 00:01:07.149
flesh two and three times a day, you

00:01:07.159 --> 00:01:08.910
need to feed your spirit, and you can't

00:01:08.920 --> 00:01:11.109
just feed it on Wednesdays and Sundays,

00:01:11.119 --> 00:01:12.670
right? So, Diana and I, we're always

00:01:12.680 --> 00:01:15.510
looking all the time for words that

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:16.789
will fan the

00:01:16.799 --> 00:01:20.550
flame. How do you keep strong in these

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:21.630
dark

00:01:21.640 --> 00:01:25.149
times? We had an election, and thank God

00:01:25.159 --> 00:01:28.910
it's over, but it's time to move on. I

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:30.590
really believe

00:01:30.600 --> 00:01:32.830
the Holy Spirit is telling me,

00:01:32.840 --> 00:01:34.350
'Brandon, let's not

00:01:34.360 --> 00:01:36.870
talk about politics no more. We're

00:01:36.870 --> 00:01:36.880
done.'We

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:39.789
saw it, we had it,

00:01:39.799 --> 00:01:42.069
and the caravan's moving on, folks.

00:01:42.079 --> 00:01:44.630
I just can't park there no more;

00:01:44.640 --> 00:01:47.310
you'll dry up spiritually. Always praying

00:01:47.320 --> 00:01:48.749
for the election, always that stuff. Yeah, we

00:01:48.759 --> 00:01:50.230
pray for our government, we pray for our

00:01:50.240 --> 00:01:52.590
leaders, but we've got to get deeper in

00:01:52.600 --> 00:01:56.630
the things of God. I noticed even

00:01:56.640 --> 00:01:58.749
with this, I did my mission, I did what

00:01:58.759 --> 00:02:01.429
He said to do, and now He's

00:02:01.439 --> 00:02:03.190
telling me, 'Brandon,

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:04.630
it's time for you to tell my people

00:02:04.640 --> 00:02:08.070
something different here.'Like

00:02:08.070 --> 00:02:08.080
we

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:11.589
say, we came, we conquered; it's

00:02:11.589 --> 00:02:11.599
time

00:02:11.599 --> 00:02:13.470
to keep

00:02:13.470 --> 00:02:13.480
climbing.

00:02:13.480 --> 00:02:15.229
We don't build a tent there;

00:02:15.239 --> 00:02:16.670
we're climbers. So it's time to keep

00:02:16.680 --> 00:02:18.509
climbing, keep on pressing on.

00:02:18.519 --> 00:02:20.030
We've

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:23.670
got to go to the

00:02:23.680 --> 00:02:27.830
summit, and I'm excited, y'all.

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:29.070
You know,

00:02:30.480 --> 00:02:34.270
the Lord was instructing me about

00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:37.550
prayer, and He was talking about staying

00:02:37.560 --> 00:02:40.030
full, being filled and controlled by the

00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:43.790
Holy Spirit, but showing me examples of

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:48.470
people who fake it a lot.

00:02:48.480 --> 00:02:52.670
You can fake being full for a season, for

00:02:52.680 --> 00:02:54.750
a little bit, and fool people

00:02:54.750 --> 00:02:54.760
because

00:02:54.760 --> 00:02:57.309
you have all the Christian

00:02:57.319 --> 00:02:59.910
lingo, the verbiage, the

00:02:59.910 --> 00:02:59.920
hallelujahs,

00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:02.270
the shouts,

00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:04.190
and you shake a little bit.

00:03:04.200 --> 00:03:07.030
You can put on a performance

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:09.589
sometimes, and people fall for it. But if

00:03:09.599 --> 00:03:12.470
you're a seasoned veteran and you're

00:03:12.480 --> 00:03:15.470
watching that, you know the difference

00:03:15.480 --> 00:03:18.110
between fake and real. You know the

00:03:18.120 --> 00:03:21.030
difference between cold and hot, even

00:03:21.040 --> 00:03:23.149
whenever they pretend they're hot. You

00:03:23.159 --> 00:03:25.149
know when they start praying if there's

00:03:25.159 --> 00:03:28.710
no well there. I

00:03:28.720 --> 00:03:31.429
heard another person stand up

00:03:31.439 --> 00:03:34.429
before and they start praying, and the

00:03:34.439 --> 00:03:37.309
glory comes into the atmosphere.

00:03:37.319 --> 00:03:39.949
You can't mock the glory. When the

00:03:39.959 --> 00:03:43.270
glory is there, there's no flesh that can

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:46.869
make that happen. It's

00:03:46.879 --> 00:03:49.030
beautiful when the spirit of the Lord

00:03:49.040 --> 00:03:51.710
comes in through prayer.

00:03:51.720 --> 00:03:54.789
It's Holy Ghost prayer versus somebody

00:03:54.799 --> 00:03:57.990
who is dry, trying to make prayer happen

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:00.589
like a counterfeit.

00:04:00.599 --> 00:04:02.429
That's why we don't want that on our

00:04:02.439 --> 00:04:04.190
channel. I don't want to

00:04:04.200 --> 00:04:07.429
waste your time. If I don't feel

00:04:07.439 --> 00:04:09.149
it... there are some days I come here and I feel

00:04:09.159 --> 00:04:11.869
dry and I just try

00:04:11.879 --> 00:04:13.710
to get through,

00:04:13.710 --> 00:04:13.720
but

00:04:13.720 --> 00:04:16.349
I don't want that. I

00:04:16.359 --> 00:04:18.830
want to be filled with and controlled by

00:04:18.840 --> 00:04:21.509
the Holy Spirit so that when you

00:04:21.519 --> 00:04:23.749
take time out of your

00:04:23.759 --> 00:04:25.990
day, you're getting a fresh touch from

00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:28.870
the Holy Spirit.

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:32.110
You walk away changed. I don't want to

00:04:32.120 --> 00:04:34.189
fall out in the Holy Ghost, shake a

00:04:34.199 --> 00:04:36.590
couple of times on the floor, and get up and

00:04:36.600 --> 00:04:39.510
be the same. No, I want

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:41.710
impartation. I want to change. I want to

00:04:41.720 --> 00:04:44.270
go from glory to glory. I don't want to

00:04:44.280 --> 00:04:47.390
play church where we

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:50.590
say a couple

00:04:50.590 --> 00:04:50.600
of

00:04:50.600 --> 00:04:53.469
whatever

00:04:53.479 --> 00:04:55.909
and we get up and we shake around

00:04:55.919 --> 00:04:57.749
and have a 'Holy Ghost

00:04:57.749 --> 00:04:57.759
thing'trying

00:04:57.759 --> 00:04:59.270
to mock what we had

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:02.830
10 years ago

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:04.390
when we were kids.

00:05:11.199 --> 00:05:12.710
The Holy Spirit wasn't in it;

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:15.950
it's just flesh. People get weird.

00:05:15.960 --> 00:05:17.950
I want

00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:20.510
something tangible, something I

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:22.670
can bite my teeth into spiritually

00:05:22.680 --> 00:05:24.469
that's going to change me and draw me

00:05:24.479 --> 00:05:27.150
closer to Him. When we found this

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:30.469
book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near', it's

00:05:30.479 --> 00:05:32.909
exactly what we needed. He

00:05:32.919 --> 00:05:35.629
didn't sponsor this;

00:05:35.639 --> 00:05:38.590
we don't even know this man. We

00:05:38.600 --> 00:05:40.670
truly believe there's something

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:42.390
in this.

00:05:45.479 --> 00:05:48.150
We've read a

00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:50.710
lot of his books

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:52.950
and they're

00:05:52.960 --> 00:05:55.590
life-changing, very anointed.

00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:57.350
Some people say, 'Well, this

00:05:57.360 --> 00:06:00.629
is old,'but I don't care how old it is.

00:06:00.639 --> 00:06:04.230
I'm extremely picky about what I

00:06:04.240 --> 00:06:08.110
read. Diana will read a couple

00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:09.430
of

00:06:09.440 --> 00:06:11.150
pages and

00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:13.469
she'll go, 'This is trash,'and throw it

00:06:13.479 --> 00:06:15.749
away. A lot of people

00:06:15.759 --> 00:06:18.070
send us books and she'll

00:06:18.080 --> 00:06:19.710
throw them away.

00:06:19.720 --> 00:06:21.029
If you don't want to have

00:06:21.039 --> 00:06:22.550
your feelings hurt, don't tell her

00:06:22.560 --> 00:06:24.469
to read your book

00:06:24.469 --> 00:06:24.479
because

00:06:24.479 --> 00:06:26.909
we're not going to

00:06:28.189 --> 00:06:28.199
sugarcoat

00:06:30.120 --> 00:06:32.510
it.

00:06:35.790 --> 00:06:35.800
You

00:06:38.599 --> 00:06:40.270
can't

00:06:42.759 --> 00:06:45.629
counterfeit the

00:06:45.639 --> 00:06:48.469
Holy Spirit. We're veterans, folks,

00:06:48.479 --> 00:06:50.589
and I'm not

00:06:50.599 --> 00:06:52.870
trying to be prideful, but

00:06:52.880 --> 00:06:54.390
I'm a veteran when it comes to knowing

00:06:54.390 --> 00:06:54.400
what's

00:06:54.400 --> 00:06:57.909
real and authentic. I know it

00:06:57.919 --> 00:07:00.309
instantaneously. I'm like a

00:07:00.309 --> 00:07:00.319
tractor

00:07:00.319 --> 00:07:03.189
beam.

00:07:03.199 --> 00:07:05.909
I just know when you know.

00:07:05.909 --> 00:07:05.919
Even

00:07:05.919 --> 00:07:07.550
when you see people behind the

00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:09.469
pulpit,

00:07:11.440 --> 00:07:13.230
you listen to them and go, 'You

00:07:13.240 --> 00:07:14.629
just need to sit

00:07:14.629 --> 00:07:14.639
down.'I'm

00:07:14.639 --> 00:07:17.749
not trying to be rude, but

00:07:17.759 --> 00:07:19.710
you're wasting people's

00:07:19.720 --> 00:07:22.510
time if you didn't take the time to fill

00:07:22.520 --> 00:07:24.469
yourself up with the Holy Ghost before

00:07:24.479 --> 00:07:27.670
you came to church. Sit down and pass

00:07:27.680 --> 00:07:29.670
the baton to somebody else.

00:07:42.960 --> 00:07:45.869
I

00:07:45.879 --> 00:07:47.710
want to go from glory to glory.

00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:52.710
We get all caught up in the politics

00:07:52.720 --> 00:07:54.270
and everything going

00:07:54.280 --> 00:07:57.830
on and we camp there, but God's

00:07:57.840 --> 00:07:59.710
wanting to move the caravan and go up

00:07:59.720 --> 00:08:01.790
the mountain now. We've got to

00:08:01.800 --> 00:08:03.550
pray for this nation,

00:08:03.560 --> 00:08:05.670
yes, but we've got to get a

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:08.270
harvest for the Kingdom; He is the

00:08:08.280 --> 00:08:10.390
Lord of the harvest.

00:08:12.319 --> 00:08:13.790
You can always tell when a

00:08:13.790 --> 00:08:13.800
book is

00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:15.909
written for

00:08:15.919 --> 00:08:17.670
money or if it's really Holy

00:08:17.680 --> 00:08:20.950
Spirit inspired.

00:08:25.120 --> 00:08:27.589
I don't want

00:08:27.599 --> 00:08:30.270
to cut you off, Diana, I'm sorry;

00:08:30.280 --> 00:08:32.430
I start rattling

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:34.469
too much. I

00:08:34.469 --> 00:08:34.479
want

00:08:34.479 --> 00:08:37.190
you

00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:39.909
to show them, babe. This is what

00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:43.670
changes you. Aren't you

00:08:43.680 --> 00:08:45.630
ready for some

00:08:45.640 --> 00:08:47.750
authentic,

00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:49.710
quit-playing-church

00:08:49.720 --> 00:08:53.590
folks? I'm tired of

00:08:53.600 --> 00:08:55.590
walking away and not having

00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:58.470
a life-experience change with

00:08:58.480 --> 00:09:00.389
the Lord.

00:09:00.399 --> 00:09:02.509
I don't want to just fall down and shake

00:09:02.519 --> 00:09:04.310
a little bit;

00:09:04.320 --> 00:09:09.310
I want to get up and go, 'My God, I'm

00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:12.630
changed.'You

00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:16.829
get lackadaisical and comfortable

00:09:16.839 --> 00:09:18.310
as you're praying for the election and

00:09:18.310 --> 00:09:18.320
all that

00:09:18.320 --> 00:09:19.389
stuff,

00:09:19.389 --> 00:09:19.399
but

00:09:19.399 --> 00:09:21.430
you always have

00:09:21.430 --> 00:09:21.440
to

00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:23.790
come back to the heartbeat of God.

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:28.389
What is He saying about this generation?

00:09:28.399 --> 00:09:30.230
Draw near.

00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:40.590
I'm desperate for a touch

00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:43.829
today.

00:09:43.839 --> 00:09:46.550
I see the emails

00:09:46.560 --> 00:09:48.269
and you're so broken; you're not

00:09:48.279 --> 00:09:50.870
getting fed at your churches. You're

00:09:50.880 --> 00:09:53.870
desperate for change,

00:09:53.880 --> 00:09:55.590
for your marriages,

00:09:55.600 --> 00:09:57.829
for healing,

00:09:57.839 --> 00:09:59.949
for all this

00:09:59.959 --> 00:10:02.550
stuff, but you're not going to the

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:05.269
Source.

00:10:05.279 --> 00:10:08.590
It's

00:10:08.590 --> 00:10:08.600
about

00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:12.550
drawing near to Him. It's being

00:10:12.560 --> 00:10:13.430
like

00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:16.430
Moses.

00:10:16.440 --> 00:10:20.389
He had everything in Egypt, just like John

00:10:20.389 --> 00:10:20.399
Bevere

00:10:20.399 --> 00:10:22.350
talks about in his book, and he never

00:10:22.360 --> 00:10:23.990
once complained about wanting to go back.

00:10:28.079 --> 00:10:30.310
He even

00:10:30.320 --> 00:10:32.630
said, 'I don't want to go to the Promised

00:10:32.640 --> 00:10:34.230
Land, I don't want to go to the next

00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:38.269
level, if You're not going with us.

00:10:38.279 --> 00:10:42.030
I would rather stay here in the

00:10:42.040 --> 00:10:45.629
desert if I don't have

00:10:45.639 --> 00:10:49.310
You.'He

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:53.430
chose the

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:57.350
desert just to stay

00:10:57.350 --> 00:10:57.360
with God.

00:10:57.360 --> 00:11:00.310
That's desperate,

00:11:00.320 --> 00:11:02.150
because the desert is not a fun

00:11:02.160 --> 00:11:05.509
place.

00:11:22.639 --> 00:11:26.470
I don't think a lot of people

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:32.350
want to go through any hard

00:11:32.350 --> 00:11:32.360
times—a

00:11:32.360 --> 00:11:35.150
financial collapse or any

00:11:35.160 --> 00:11:37.509
craziness—because

00:11:37.519 --> 00:11:39.590
anytime I bring it up, people say, 'Oh my

00:11:39.600 --> 00:11:41.310
God, I rebuke

00:11:41.310 --> 00:11:41.320
that.'But

00:11:41.320 --> 00:11:42.470
the

00:11:42.480 --> 00:11:44.430
Lord said to keep doing the same thing

00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:49.069
and asking for something different is

00:11:49.079 --> 00:11:51.910
insanity. We want change, we want the

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:54.110
glory, we want revival. I had a

00:11:54.110 --> 00:11:54.120
mega-minister

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:57.150
text me tonight

00:11:57.160 --> 00:12:01.069
asking,

00:12:01.079 --> 00:12:02.550
'Where's the glory?

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:05.030
Why haven't we seen it?

00:12:05.040 --> 00:12:06.550
What's the

00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:08.269
hold-up?'That's

00:12:11.870 --> 00:12:11.880
a

00:12:15.959 --> 00:12:19.069
great question. Where is

00:12:19.079 --> 00:12:20.310
the

00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:22.829
revival? Where is the presence of the

00:12:22.839 --> 00:12:24.790
Lord in the churches?

00:12:36.360 --> 00:12:39.790
Do

00:12:39.800 --> 00:12:41.430
you know of anything real

00:12:41.440 --> 00:12:43.030
happening? We had something

00:12:43.040 --> 00:12:45.710
at the tent revival a couple of weeks ago, but

00:12:45.720 --> 00:12:48.590
I haven't heard of anything

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:51.310
since we focused on the election. We got

00:12:51.320 --> 00:12:52.550
what we

00:12:52.560 --> 00:12:55.269
wanted, and now we have the ability to

00:12:55.279 --> 00:12:57.509
turn around, but we don't want to

00:12:57.519 --> 00:12:59.870
change. They don't want to let go of

00:12:59.880 --> 00:13:01.189
their seeker-friendly message with

00:13:01.199 --> 00:13:04.509
skinny jeans and fog machines.

00:13:06.720 --> 00:13:09.150
They're like Moses's people—they choose to stay back. Moses

00:13:10.959 --> 00:13:14.389
went

00:13:16.519 --> 00:13:18.750
up on the mountain

00:13:18.750 --> 00:13:18.760
for

00:13:18.760 --> 00:13:21.230
40 days, and they all

00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:24.150
had the ability to come up with him; the

00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:26.310
Lord invited every single one of them to

00:13:26.320 --> 00:13:27.670
have a relationship with

00:13:27.680 --> 00:13:29.710
Him.

00:13:29.720 --> 00:13:32.910
But they chose to send Moses because it

00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:36.310
was uncomfortable to their flesh.

00:13:38.199 --> 00:13:41.550
Aaron didn't

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:43.430
go.

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:46.550
Joshua had more fear of the Lord;

